<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14102">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b
        >NOTE: Scouts should obey all local fishing regulations and property
        laws.</b
      >
      <br /><br />
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Fly-Fishing.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11386">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11386 mb-requirement-id-11387">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in fly-fishing activities and what you should do to
        anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards. Name
        and explain five safety practices you should always follow while
        fly-fishing. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://anglersadvantageguideservice.com/why-is-fishing-dangerous-dont-overlook-these-risks/"
          target="_blank"
          >Why Is Fishing Dangerous? Don't Overlook These Risks! (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PiSbKetM50U" target="_blank"
          >Wader Safety 101 (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11386 mb-requirement-id-11388">
        (b) Discuss the prevention of and treatment for the following health
        concerns that could occur while fly-fishing: cuts and scratches,
        puncture wounds, insect bites, hypothermia, dehydration, heat
        exhaustion, heatstroke, and sunburn. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/L6crQ3nMLkI" target="_blank"
          >Splinters (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0jp5FgLmKtk" target="_blank"
          >How To Treat Cuts and Bruises (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YkUW3pquCF4" target="_blank"
          >How To Treat an Insect Bite or Sting | First Aid Training (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/my6JB41apTw" target="_blank"
          >Hypothermia (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KahsIEbFROI" target="_blank"
          >What Is Dehydration? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8gn3DEYOPuE" target="_blank"
          >Heat Exhaustion vs Heat Stroke (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-KzTvagnpfU" target="_blank"
          >Sunburn (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11386 mb-requirement-id-11389">
        (c) Explain how to remove a hook that has lodged in someone's arm.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/AmT3T_9Guq0" target="_blank"
          >Removing a Fishhook (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/52GLMQp52qg" target="_blank"
          >How To Remove a Hook (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11401">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Demonstrate how to match a fly rod, line, and leader to achieve a balanced
      system. Discuss several types of fly lines, and explain how and when each
      would be used. Review with your counselor how to care for this equipment.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/AzmVg3rN08U" target="_blank"
        >How To Set Up a Fly Rod and Reel (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/w_5V08fYXnQ" target="_blank"
        >How To Set Up Your Fly Line, Leader, Tippet, &amp; Flies (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/zYlWyySamYk" target="_blank"
        >Understanding Fly Line Tapers (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/j7w6LEpbLeo" target="_blank"
        >Cleaning and Maintaining Your Fly Fishing Gear (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11390">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Demonstrate how to tie proper knots to prepare a fly rod for fishing:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11390 mb-requirement-id-11391">
        (a) Tie backing to the arbor of a fly reel spool using an arbor knot.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.netknots.com/fishing_knots/arbor-knot"
          target="_blank"
          >Arbor Knot (website/video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11390 mb-requirement-id-11392">
        (b) Tie backing to the fly line using a nail (tube) knot. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.netknots.com/fishing_knots/nail-knot"
          target="_blank"
          >Nail Knot (website/video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11390 mb-requirement-id-11393">
        (c) Attach a leader to the fly line using a nail (tube) knot or a
        loop-to-loop connection. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.netknots.com/fishing_knots/loop-to-loop-knot"
          target="_blank"
          >Loop to Loop Knot (website/video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11390 mb-requirement-id-11394">
        (d) Add a tippet to a leader using a surgeon's knot or a loop-to-loop
        connection. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.netknots.com/fishing_knots/surgeons-knot"
          target="_blank"
          >Surgeon's Knot (website/video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11390 mb-requirement-id-11395">
        (e) Tie a fly onto the terminal end of the leader using an improved
        clinch knot. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.netknots.com/fishing_knots/improved-clinch-knot"
          target="_blank"
          >Improved Clinch Knot (website/video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11402">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Explain how and when each of the following types of flies is used: dry
      flies, wet flies, nymphs, streamers, bass bugs, poppers, and saltwater
      flies. Tell what each one imitates. Tie at least two types of the flies
      mentioned in this requirement. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/jz189rWAMfw" target="_blank"
        >Fly Fishing Flies Explained (Streamers, Nymphs, Dry Flies &amp; More)
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/yoR-cDYRAiE" target="_blank"
        >Bass Popper Fly—Bass Series:McFly Angler fly Tying Tutorial (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/OuWR6Zx1MaQ" target="_blank"
        >Saltwater Flys (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11403">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Demonstrate the ability to cast a fly 30 feet consistently and accurately
      using both overhead and roll cast techniques. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ey2DSp3_s6E" target="_blank"
        >Overhead Cast and Roll Cast (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11404">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Go to a suitable fishing location and observe what fish may be eating both
      above and beneath the water's surface. Explain the importance of matching
      the hatch. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/TdV0DMk6ohs" target="_blank"
        >Match the Hatch Fly Fishing (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11396">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11396 mb-requirement-id-11397">
        (a) Explain the importance of practicing Leave No Trace Seven Principles
        and the Outdoor Code. Discuss the positive effects of the Leave No Trace
        Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code on fly-fishing resources. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Rpq01rO9ZR0" target="_blank"
          >What Is Leave No trace? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://lnt.org/why/7-principles/" target="_blank"
          >7 Principles—Leave No Trace (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://vimeo.com/1115216743/63b20c0b33?share=copy"
          target="_blank"
          >LNT Basics (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11396 mb-requirement-id-11398">
        (b) Discuss the meaning and importance of catch and release. Describe
        how to properly release a fish safely to the water. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/MBg_dtAY2-o" target="_blank"
          >Proper Catch and Release Fishing Practices (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TzNjYoRpvb0" target="_blank"
          >How To Safely Handle Fish for Catch &amp; Release Fishing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SMGO50R_lrA" target="_blank"
          >Ethical Catch and Release (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11405">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Obtain and review a copy of the regulations affecting game fishing where
      you live or where you plan to fish. Explain why they were adopted and what
      is accomplished by following them. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://fishpiers.com/fishing-license-requirements-by-state-all-50-states/"
        target="_blank"
        >Fishing Licenses, Rules, Regulations (web)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11406">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Explain what good outdoor sportsmanlike behavior is and how it relates to
      anglers. Tell how the Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code
      relate to a fishing sports enthusiast, including the aspects of littering,
      trespassing, courteous behavior, and obeying fishing regulations. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/54ImytCqbzI" target="_blank"
        >Understanding Basic Fishing Rules and Etiquette (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/HGJc_mb9InY" target="_blank"
        >Fly Fishing Guidelines with Leave No Trace (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11399">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Catch one fish on a fly and identify it. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://freeappsforme.com/fish-identification-apps/"
        target="_blank"
        >Fish Identification Apps (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/mZ4M-AP6-iQ" target="_blank"
        >How To Identify Common Freshwater Fish (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11400">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      If regulations and health concerns permit, clean and cook a fish you have
      caught. If you are unable to catch a fish for eating, acquire a fish,
      clean the fish you acquired, and cook the fish you acquired. <br /><b
        >Note:
      </b>
      It is not required that you eat the fish. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ZiGEN2F_spc" target="_blank"
        >How To Clean, Descale, and Gut a Fresh Fish (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/uBDYqh8p2fU" target="_blank"
        >How To Clean and Care for Your Catch (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/hca5xiZbulY?feature=share"
        target="_blank"
        >How To Fillet a Fish (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/u19fJ10kAVo?feature=share"
        target="_blank"
        >How To Clean a Fish Before Cooking (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/BSQhEjSalwk" target="_blank"
        >How To Cook a Fish (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Tgv7tCx2NsA" target="_blank"
        >5 Easy Ways To Cook Fish (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
